cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a deep generative model for face completion, which involves generating new pixels for missing key components. This task falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves training a neural network. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of adversarial losses and semantic parsing, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The generated faces are also evaluated qualitatively and quantitatively, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) research.
